## Pass 3 Complete: Design Consistency Audit

**Build: PASS** (72/72 pages generated)

### Summary of fixes across 6 files:

1. **Color unification** — Blog, FAQ, and Products pages were using 3 different off-brand accent colors (`#C9DD69`, `#B8923A`, `#C9A24B`). All replaced with the site's `#A4B08A` olive accent defined in `globals.css`.

2. **Heading weight normalization** — Science page had contradicting `font-bold` class + `fontWeight: 200` inline (inline wins, creating ultra-thin headings that don't match the site). Blog and FAQ used `fontWeight: 200-300`. Build Your Stack used `font-bold`. All normalized to `font-medium` (500) matching the homepage and product pages.

3. **Eyebrow standardization** — Science, Blog, and FAQ used custom inline eyebrow styles with varying sizes/weights/tracking. Replaced with the `.eyebrow` CSS class.

4. **Border radius** — Blog cards used `rounded-sm` (2px) while every other card on the site uses `rounded-lg` (8px). Fixed.

5. **Section padding** — Blog sections used `py-14 md:py-16` (much tighter) vs the site standard `py-20 md:py-28`. Fixed.

6. **Tailwind gray utilities** — Build Your Stack used `text-gray-600/500/400` and `bg-gray-200` instead of the site's color tokens. Replaced with `text-[#555]`, `text-[#888]`, `text-[#AAA]`, `bg-[#E8E5E0]`.

7. **Button consistency** — Blog CTAs used custom inline-styled buttons. Replaced with `btn-primary` class.

